{"lastModified":1777306006144,"value":{"kind":"PAGE","html":"<!DOCTYPE html><html lang=\"en\"><head><meta charSet=\"utf-8\"/><meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\"/><link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"/_next/static/css/2bc5eb976236e772.css\" data-precedence=\"next\"/><link rel=\"preload\" as=\"script\" fetchPriority=\"low\" href=\"/_next/static/chunks/webpack-cb86a99cd2f791d1.js\"/><script src=\"/_next/static/chunks/fd9d1056-83701e137505fb90.js\" async=\"\"></script><script src=\"/_next/static/chunks/23-d69ab8120dffc5ff.js\" async=\"\"></script><script src=\"/_next/static/chunks/main-app-53416707d9ca77c7.js\" async=\"\"></script><script src=\"/_next/static/chunks/231-e7502a79afe5754f.js\" async=\"\"></script><script src=\"/_next/static/chunks/173-18d687d87bb09bf0.js\" async=\"\"></script><script src=\"/_next/static/chunks/app/samples/page-2b097652b669e7d7.js\" async=\"\"></script><title>PageCub - Personalized illustrated storybooks</title><meta name=\"description\" content=\"A custom illustrated adventure made around your child.\"/><script src=\"/_next/static/chunks/polyfills-78c92fac7aa8fdd8.js\" noModule=\"\"></script></head><body><header class=\"sticky top-0 z-50 border-b border-line/70 bg-cream/90 backdrop-blur\"><nav class=\"page-shell flex min-h-20 items-center justify-between gap-4\"><a class=\"flex items-center gap-3 font-bold text-ink\" aria-label=\"PageCub home\" href=\"/\"><span class=\"flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-honey text-ink shadow-sm\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-book-open h-5 w-5\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M12 7v14\"></path><path d=\"M3 18a1 1 0 0 1-1-1V4a1 1 0 0 1 1-1h5a4 4 0 0 1 4 4 4 4 0 0 1 4-4h5a1 1 0 0 1 1 1v13a1 1 0 0 1-1 1h-6a3 3 0 0 0-3 3 3 3 0 0 0-3-3z\"></path></svg></span><span class=\"display text-2xl\">PageCub</span></a><div class=\"hidden items-center gap-7 text-sm font-semibold text-ink/75 md:flex\"><a class=\"transition hover:text-ink\" href=\"/how-it-works\">How it works</a><a class=\"transition hover:text-ink\" href=\"/samples\">Samples</a><a class=\"transition hover:text-ink\" href=\"/pricing\">Pricing</a><a class=\"transition hover:text-ink\" href=\"/faq\">FAQ</a></div><a class=\"inline-flex min-h-11 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-ink px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-bold text-white transition hover:-translate-y-0.5\" href=\"/create\">Start a Book</a></nav></header><main class=\"page-shell py-14\"><div class=\"max-w-3xl\"><p class=\"font-bold text-sage\">Sample book</p><h1 class=\"display mt-3 text-5xl font-bold\">Aurelia and the Moonlight Kingdom</h1><p class=\"mt-5 text-lg leading-8 text-ink/72\">You&#x27;ll notice most of our examples follow the same little girl, Aurelia. That&#x27;s my daughter. I originally built PageCub because I wanted to make her books - stories built around whatever she was going through, whatever she was into, whatever she couldn&#x27;t find on the shelf. She was the first reader. She still is.</p></div><div class=\"mt-10 flex flex-wrap gap-3\"><a href=\"#chapter-1\" class=\"rounded-full border border-line bg-card px-4 py-2 text-sm font-bold\">Chapter <!-- -->1<!-- -->: <!-- -->Not Sleepy Yet</a><a href=\"#chapter-3\" class=\"rounded-full border border-line bg-card px-4 py-2 text-sm font-bold\">Chapter <!-- -->3<!-- -->: <!-- -->A Tiny Dragon Friend</a><a href=\"#chapter-5\" class=\"rounded-full border border-line bg-card px-4 py-2 text-sm font-bold\">Chapter <!-- -->5<!-- -->: <!-- -->The Sleeping Star</a></div><div class=\"mt-12 grid gap-12\"><section id=\"chapter-1\" class=\"rounded-[2rem] border border-line bg-card p-4 shadow-soft md:p-7\"><div class=\"mb-6\"><p class=\"text-sm font-bold text-sage\">Chapter <!-- -->1</p><h2 class=\"display mt-1 text-3xl font-bold\">Not Sleepy Yet</h2><p class=\"mt-3 max-w-3xl text-sm leading-6 text-ink/70\">Aurelia is bursting with energy at bedtime and tells Mama she cannot possibly sleep because she heard a dragon outside her window.</p></div><div class=\"grid gap-5\"><article class=\"grid overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-line md:grid-cols-2\"><div class=\"book-paper p-6 md:p-8\"><p class=\"mb-4 text-sm font-bold text-ink/55\">Page <!-- -->1</p><p class=\"whitespace-pre-line text-[15px] leading-7 text-ink/78\">Aurelia was NOT sleepy. Not even a little bit.\n\nShe stood in her favorite yellow dress and her rainbow rainboots. Her brown hair tumbled past her shoulders, curling at the tips, half of it flopping right over one eye the way it always did.\n\nShe bounced on her toes. She wiggled her fingers. She made a silly face at her stuffed bunny.\n\n&quot;Bedtime, sweet girl!&quot; Mama called from the doorway.\n\nAurelia&#x27;s big blue-grey eyes went wide. Her mouth stretched into the biggest grin you ever saw, the kind that showed her one special dimple on her right cheek.\n\n&quot;But Mama,&quot; she said, &quot;I can&#x27;t go to bed yet!&quot;</p></div><img alt=\"Not Sleepy Yet illustration page 1\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"720\" height=\"720\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" class=\"h-full min-h-80 w-full object-cover\" style=\"color:transparent\" srcSet=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2F9c16f3e2-632d-432a-858a-4cac45f62abc.webp&amp;w=750&amp;q=75 1x, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2F9c16f3e2-632d-432a-858a-4cac45f62abc.webp&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75 2x\" src=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2F9c16f3e2-632d-432a-858a-4cac45f62abc.webp&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75\"/></article><article class=\"grid overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-line md:grid-cols-2\"><div class=\"book-paper p-6 md:p-8\"><p class=\"mb-4 text-sm font-bold text-ink/55\">Page <!-- -->2</p><p class=\"whitespace-pre-line text-[15px] leading-7 text-ink/78\">Mama put her hands on her hips and tried not to smile. &quot;And why not?&quot;\n\nAurelia leaned in close, like she had the most important secret in the whole world. She cupped her hands around her mouth and whispered very loudly.\n\n&quot;I think I heard a DRAGON outside!&quot;\n\nShe pointed one finger straight at her window. Her eyes sparkled. Her dimple deepened.\n\nMama shook her head and laughed. &quot;A dragon, huh?&quot;\n\n&quot;A real one, Mama! With wings and everything!&quot; Aurelia bounced again, her rainbow rainboots thumping on the floor. &quot;I have to go check. I just HAVE to.&quot;\n\nShe was already tiptoeing toward the window, fingers reaching for the curtain. Something outside glowed soft and silver, just behind the glass.</p></div><img alt=\"Not Sleepy Yet illustration page 2\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"720\" height=\"720\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" class=\"h-full min-h-80 w-full object-cover\" style=\"color:transparent\" srcSet=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2F3ff76772-2259-4669-8601-0a4ddbbd4732.webp&amp;w=750&amp;q=75 1x, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2F3ff76772-2259-4669-8601-0a4ddbbd4732.webp&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75 2x\" src=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2F3ff76772-2259-4669-8601-0a4ddbbd4732.webp&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75\"/></article></div></section><section id=\"chapter-3\" class=\"rounded-[2rem] border border-line bg-card p-4 shadow-soft md:p-7\"><div class=\"mb-6\"><p class=\"text-sm font-bold text-sage\">Chapter <!-- -->3</p><h2 class=\"display mt-1 text-3xl font-bold\">A Tiny Dragon Friend</h2><p class=\"mt-3 max-w-3xl text-sm leading-6 text-ink/70\">Aurelia climbs through her window onto the golden path of the Moonlight Kingdom and meets a tiny friendly dragon who lands on her shoulder and becomes her companion.</p></div><div class=\"grid gap-5\"><article class=\"grid overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-line md:grid-cols-2\"><div class=\"book-paper p-6 md:p-8\"><p class=\"mb-4 text-sm font-bold text-ink/55\">Page <!-- -->1</p><p class=\"whitespace-pre-line text-[15px] leading-7 text-ink/78\">Aurelia giggled and climbed right through the window onto the sparkly golden path.\n\nHer rainbow rainboots went crunch, crunch on the glittering ground. The air smelled like warm cookies and fresh rain all swirled together.\n\nTiny star-flowers tickled her ankles as she walked. Everything glowed soft and silver under the big round moon.\n\nThen she heard a little sound above her. Fwip, fwip, fwip. Something small was flying down from the sky, coming closer and closer.\n\nAurelia looked up and held very still.</p></div><img alt=\"A Tiny Dragon Friend illustration page 1\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"720\" height=\"720\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" class=\"h-full min-h-80 w-full object-cover\" style=\"color:transparent\" srcSet=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2Fb4bcb09e-a0f2-4ec4-8a9f-434c3f2991f1.webp&amp;w=750&amp;q=75 1x, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2Fb4bcb09e-a0f2-4ec4-8a9f-434c3f2991f1.webp&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75 2x\" src=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2Fb4bcb09e-a0f2-4ec4-8a9f-434c3f2991f1.webp&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75\"/></article><article class=\"grid overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-line md:grid-cols-2\"><div class=\"book-paper p-6 md:p-8\"><p class=\"mb-4 text-sm font-bold text-ink/55\">Page <!-- -->2</p><p class=\"whitespace-pre-line text-[15px] leading-7 text-ink/78\">A tiny dragon landed right on her shoulder!\n\nHe was no bigger than a kitten, with shimmery green and gold scales and big round eyes that blinked at her. His little wings folded up neatly against his back.\n\n&quot;Hello!&quot; said Aurelia.\n\nThe dragon tilted his head. Then he purred, soft and rumbly, like a happy cat.\n\nAurelia reached up and gently scratched under his chin. He closed his eyes and leaned into her fingers. His scales felt warm and smooth, like river stones in the sun.\n\n&quot;I think we&#x27;re going to be friends,&quot; Aurelia whispered.\n\nThe little dragon chirped. Together they looked down the golden path winding deeper into the kingdom.</p></div><img alt=\"A Tiny Dragon Friend illustration page 2\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"720\" height=\"720\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" class=\"h-full min-h-80 w-full object-cover\" style=\"color:transparent\" srcSet=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2F74aca76d-d514-414c-957b-a5984c77f9ed.webp&amp;w=750&amp;q=75 1x, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2F74aca76d-d514-414c-957b-a5984c77f9ed.webp&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75 2x\" src=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2F74aca76d-d514-414c-957b-a5984c77f9ed.webp&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75\"/></article></div></section><section id=\"chapter-5\" class=\"rounded-[2rem] border border-line bg-card p-4 shadow-soft md:p-7\"><div class=\"mb-6\"><p class=\"text-sm font-bold text-sage\">Chapter <!-- -->5</p><h2 class=\"display mt-1 text-3xl font-bold\">The Sleeping Star</h2><p class=\"mt-3 max-w-3xl text-sm leading-6 text-ink/70\">Hazel points out the Sleeping Star, which has gone dim and left the Moonlight Kingdom in darkness.</p></div><div class=\"grid gap-5\"><article class=\"grid overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-line md:grid-cols-2\"><div class=\"book-paper p-6 md:p-8\"><p class=\"mb-4 text-sm font-bold text-ink/55\">Page <!-- -->1</p><p class=\"whitespace-pre-line text-[15px] leading-7 text-ink/78\">Aurelia&#x27;s eyes went wide. &quot;Help you?&quot; she asked.\n\nHazel nodded and pointed up at the sky. High above the kingdom, one little star hung among all the others. But this star was different. It was pale and dim, and its tiny eyes were closed tight.\n\n&quot;That is the Sleeping Star,&quot; said Hazel. &quot;It used to glow so bright and warm that every creature in the kingdom felt safe at night. But now it has fallen asleep, and it won&#x27;t wake up.&quot;\n\nAurelia looked down at the kingdom below. Little houses sat in shadows. Tiny faces peeked from dark windows, looking worried and small.\n\nThe little dragon on her shoulder gave a soft, sad chirp.</p></div><img alt=\"The Sleeping Star illustration page 1\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"720\" height=\"720\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" class=\"h-full min-h-80 w-full object-cover\" style=\"color:transparent\" srcSet=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2F16b5898f-82be-4cea-a55a-a681626f723b.webp&amp;w=750&amp;q=75 1x, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2F16b5898f-82be-4cea-a55a-a681626f723b.webp&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75 2x\" src=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2F16b5898f-82be-4cea-a55a-a681626f723b.webp&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75\"/></article><article class=\"grid overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-line md:grid-cols-2\"><div class=\"book-paper p-6 md:p-8\"><p class=\"mb-4 text-sm font-bold text-ink/55\">Page <!-- -->2</p><p class=\"whitespace-pre-line text-[15px] leading-7 text-ink/78\">&quot;Without the star&#x27;s glow, the whole kingdom stays dark,&quot; Hazel said quietly. &quot;All the little creatures are too scared to close their eyes. They need that gentle light to feel safe.&quot;\n\nAurelia knew that feeling. Sometimes her own room felt too dark at night.\n\nShe looked at the tiny faces in the windows. A fluffy owl with round worried eyes. A bunny hugging its own ears. A little mushroom fellow hiding behind a flower pot.\n\nHer heart squeezed.\n\n&quot;Someone needs to climb the tall hill and wake that star,&quot; said Hazel, looking right at Aurelia.\n\nAurelia swallowed. The hill was very, very tall. But those little creatures needed help.\n\n&quot;Maybe,&quot; she whispered, &quot;maybe I could try.&quot;</p></div><img alt=\"The Sleeping Star illustration page 2\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"720\" height=\"720\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" class=\"h-full min-h-80 w-full object-cover\" style=\"color:transparent\" srcSet=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2Fd0d65b15-77c2-4772-b631-c69ddd3f8198.webp&amp;w=750&amp;q=75 1x, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2Fd0d65b15-77c2-4772-b631-c69ddd3f8198.webp&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75 2x\" src=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2Fd0d65b15-77c2-4772-b631-c69ddd3f8198.webp&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75\"/></article></div></section></div><div class=\"mt-12 rounded-[2rem] bg-sage/18 p-8 text-center\"><h2 class=\"display text-3xl font-bold\">Make a book around your child</h2><p class=\"mx-auto mt-3 max-w-xl text-ink/70\">Choose the world, the lesson, the people, and the tiny details that make it feel like home.</p><div class=\"mt-7\"><a class=\"inline-flex min-h-12 items-center justify-center gap-2 rounded-full px-6 py-3 text-sm font-bold transition bg-honey text-ink shadow-button hover:-translate-y-0.5\" href=\"/create\">Start a Book<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-arrow-right h-4 w-4\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path 